From: tonytranrp <100391458+tonytranrp@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Mon, 15 Jun 2026 01:40:39 -1000
Subject: [PATCH] clang-mg: add compact x type-expression interaction test

A compact struct whose field type is a C++MG type-expression composed record (C = A + B). The composed type keeps its own source-order layout while the compact outer struct reorders its fields treating the composed field by its alignment and size. Ground truth from the layout dump.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

diff --git a/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-type-expression-field.cpp b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-type-expression-field.cpp
new file mode 100644
index 000000000..92a958aa2
--- /dev/null
+++ b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-type-expression-field.cpp
@@ -0,0 +1,26 @@
+// HARD interaction: a compact struct whose field type is a C++MG type-EXPRESSION
+// composed record (C = A + B, which concatenates A's then B's fields). The
+// composed type C keeps its own source-order (non-compact) layout, and the outer
+// compact D reorders its own fields treating C by C's alignment (8) and size
+// (24): the field order becomes {inner(C), n, tag}.
+//
+// RUN: %clang_cc1 -std=c++20 -fcxxmg -fsyntax-only -fdump-record-layouts %s | FileCheck %s
+
+struct A { char a; double b; };
+struct B { char c; int d; };
+using C = A + B;
+
+compact struct D {
+  char tag;
+  C inner;
+  int n;
+};
+D d;
+
+static_assert(sizeof(C) == 24, "composed A+B keeps source order: char,double,char,int");
+static_assert(sizeof(D) == 32, "compact reorders to {inner(24), n(4), tag(1)} -> 32");
+
+// CHECK:      struct D
+// CHECK:      0 |{{.*}}struct C inner
+// CHECK:      24 |{{.*}}int n
+// CHECK:      28 |{{.*}}char tag
-- 
